subSubSection.paragraph:
Description
. 
Male
(
Holotype
). Total length 1.1. Carapace length 0.5, ovoid; narrowing gradually anteriorly; yellow, flat pars cephalic, fovea absent (
Fig. 12A
). Clypeus length 0.02, with a pair of long bristles (
Fig. 14C
). Eyes with black border; PME oval; ALE and PLE rounded, ranging from opalescent or white (
Fig. 14C
). Chelicerae yellow; promargin with six teeth, attached to a very long lamina (
Fig. 13A
); retromargin without teeth. Sternum yellow. Endites yellow, with large serrula with more than 15 denticles, distal macrosetae paired and crosier-like, many multifid macrosetae present. Labium yellow, sulcated distally. Legs cream; formula 4123; total length: I 1.8; II 1.7; III 1.5; IV 2.1. Male palp: palpal femur length 0.03; palpal tibia enlarged basally; cymbium conical distally, bearing subdistal pair of modified setae and a projected and bifid tarsal organ (
Fig. 13D
); bulb spherical 

Fig. 12B 
–
D

); conductor shorter than SCI conic at tip (

Figs 12E 
–
F

; 
13E
; 

14A 
–
B

); embolus with short and truncated at tip SCII, short, with micro projections SCIII and long and laminar SCIV, partially covered by conductor (

Figs 12E 
–
F

; 
13F
). Abdomen length 0.45, oval; uniformly grayish (
Fig. 12A
). Two epiandrous spigots, with large, conic and striated base (
Fig. 13B
). Colulus triangular with seven bristles (
Fig. 13C
).

Female ( Paratype , IBSP 264256). Total length: 1.05; carapace length: 0.5. Carapace as in male, light yellow pattern ( Fig. 15A ). Pedipalp without claw, with conical tip and subdistal bifid tarsal organ, tibiae with four dorsal trichobothria ( Fig. 16A ). Clypeus: 0.02 diameter, with setae as in male. Eyes, chelicerae, sternum, endites and labium as in male. Legs as in male; formula 4123, total length: I 1.95; II 1.8; III 1.65; IV 2.15. Abdomen length 0.6. Colulus triangular with 6 – 7 bristles ( Fig. 16B ). Genitalia externally with distally curved lateral plates, large ventral plate and terminal depression excavates ( Figs 15D ;
16C – D
); internally with together and rounded spermathecae, and afferent spermathecae truncated distally (
Fig. 15E – F
).
